  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink288-kilavi">kiḷikaḷ puṉattiṉ kaṇ paṭiyāniṉṟaṉa eṉṟu talaiviyaik kākka ēviya vaḻi yataṉai yaṟinta talaimakaṉ uvantu taṉ neñciṟkuc colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en"> 
          What the hero, who learnt that the heroine had been ordered to guard [the millet], [as she was] told that the parakeets keep descending on the millet field, rejoiced and spoke to his heart.
          </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink288">
<l>naṉṟē ceyta vutavi naṉṟuterin</l>
<l>tiyāmevaṉ ceykuva neñcē kāmar</l>
<l>melliyaṟ koṭicci kāppap</l>
<l>palkura lēṉaṟ pāttaruṅ kiḷiyē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>O heart, having clearly understood the help they have well rendered—</l>
        <l>the parakeets that haunt the many-eared millet,</l>
        <l>while the tender, creeper-like girl keeps watch against them,</l> 
        <l>what shall we do for them in return?</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
